10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. SE Ranking is best suited for small agencies, freelancers, SMBs, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Semrush, meanwhile, shines for SEO professionals, digital agencies, marketing teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, SE Ranking describes itself as \"Affordable all-in-one SEO platform with accurate rank tracking.\" Semrush, established in 2008, positions itself as \"All-in-one digital marketing toolkit with powerful SEO and competitive analysis.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Semrush** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 8.0). However, this does not mean SE Ranking is a poor choice — far from it. SE Ranking excels in its own right, particularly for small agencies and freelancers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value most comprehensive seo toolkit available, go with Semrush. If excellent value for an all-in-one tool matters more to you, SE Ranking is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
